            <h2>Install &amp; Start</h2>
            <p>

                The fastest way to get started is to install Claude Code globally with npm and then run it inside any project directory.
                <ul>
                    <li>Requires Node.js 18 or newer.</li>
                    <li>Install: <code>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code></li>
                    <li>Go to your project: <code>cd your-project</code></li>
                    <li>Launch it: <code>claude</code></li>
                </ul>
                On first launch, Claude Code walks you through authentication &mdash; you can log in with a Claude account (Pro/Max plan) or an Anthropic API key. After that, just describe what you want in plain language, for example: <em>"explain the auth flow"</em> or <em>"add a dark mode toggle and run the tests"</em>.
                A few handy startup flags:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>claude</code> &mdash; start an interactive session</li>
                    <li><code>claude "your prompt"</code> &mdash; run a one-off task</li>
                    <li><code>claude -c</code> &mdash; continue the most recent conversation</li>
                    <li><code>claude --help</code> &mdash; list all options</li>
                </ul>

            </p>
